|GKB-- Mastery And Study -----------------------------------------|000

The mysteries of Gaea are many, and not easily understood.  Every
secret discovered reveals a new question, a possible point of
further study.  Druids now shape their craft through nwyfre
invocations and rituals.

Invocation mastery still has five levels.  The first level is
basic knowledge: the druid can invoke the power at minimum
effectiveness.  Deeper mastery improves the effect, duration,
or recovery of that invocation depending on its nature.

In order to learn an invocation, your Druid guild level must be
equal to the level listed in |CKBdhelp spells|000.  For each additional
level of mastery, your Druid guild level must be one higher.

Use |CKBdscore|000 to see study points, learned invocations, Sacred
Grove state, and profession-material guidance.  Use |CKBnwyfre|000
to see your current spirit vessels, active rites, planet, time, and
conjunction state.

Invocations may only be studied at the Druid Grove inside the
guild hall.  Rituals are learned there with:

  |CKBlearn ritual <name>|000

New druids should read:

  |CKBdhelp beginner|000
